Q: How to extract only text from HTML string with PHP? A: <p>For the middle ground between using a library and just plain <code>strip_tags</code>, here's a rough function that makes compromises that may not hurt your use case all that much, and that you can customize to your liking.</p>
<pre class="lang-php prettyprint-override"><code>/**
 * Approximately convert an HTML string to just its text content.
 *
 * Does not account for:
 * - Tag-specific styling (list, table, heading, etc.)
 * - CSS-based or style-attribute-based styling (display, visibility, etc.)
 * - Metadata nature of &lt;meta&gt;, &lt;style&gt;, &lt;script&gt;, etc. - all the nested text is included.
 * - Retaining hrefs from &lt;a&gt; tags - The url is lost in cases like &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.example.com/my-path&quot;&gt;My Site&lt;/a&gt;.
 */
function getTextContentFromHtml(string $html): string
{
    $commonLineBreakTags = implode('|', ['p', 'div', 'h1', 'h2', 'h3', 'h4', 'h5', 'h6', 'pre', 'hr', 'li']);

    // Prepend a space to line-break-triggering tags so that text like
    // &lt;p&gt;Hello&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;World&lt;/p&gt; doesn't end up as &quot;HelloWorld&quot;.
    $html = preg_replace('/(&lt;('.$commonLineBreakTags.')[^&gt;]*&gt;)/', ' $1', $html);

    // Convert &lt;br&gt; tags to newlines
    $html = preg_replace('/&lt;br ?\/?&gt;/', &quot;\n&quot;, $html);

    // Strip all tags
    $html = strip_tags($html);

    // Decode HTML entities
    $html = html_entity_decode($html, ENT_QUOTES | ENT_HTML5, 'UTF-8');

    // Convert non-breaking spaces to regular spaces
    $html = str_replace(&quot;\u{00A0}&quot;, ' ', $html);

    // Collapse extra spacing
    $html = preg_replace('/ +/', ' ', $html);
    $html = preg_replace('/\s*\n+\s*/', &quot;\n&quot;, $html);

    return trim($html);
}

echo getTextContentFromHtml('&lt;p&gt;Hello&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;World&lt;/p&gt;') . PHP_EOL; // &quot;Hello World&quot;
echo getTextContentFromHtml('Hello &amp;amp; World') . PHP_EOL; // &quot;Hello &amp; World&quot;

</code></pre>

Q: Get the first element of an array A: <p>Just trying to improve the other answers.</p>
<p>Starting from PHP 8.5+, use the very efficient <a href="https://www.php.net/manual/en/function.array-first.php" rel="nofollow noreferrer"><strong><code>array_first</code></strong></a> function:</p>
<pre class="lang-php prettyprint-override"><code>$array = array( 4 =&gt; 'apple', 7 =&gt; 'orange', 13 =&gt; 'plum' );
echo array_first($array); // outputs 'apple'
</code></pre>
<p>For older PHP versions here's a compatibility shim:</p>
<pre class="lang-php prettyprint-override"><code>if (!function_exists('array_first')) {
    // For PHP &lt; 8.5
    function array_first($array)
    {
        foreach ($array as $item) {
            return $item;
        }
        return null;
    }
}
</code></pre>

Q: Take in multiple numeric inputs and sum in javascript automatically when input is changed A: <p>Your code is pretty close to achieving what you need, you've just made a slight mistake: you've put the <em>listener</em> on the wrong element (<strong>findiv</strong>), when you should have put it on the elements you expect to change, those belonging to the <strong>.fin</strong> class.</p>
<p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false" data-console="true" data-babel="false" data-babel-preset-react="false" data-babel-preset-ts="false">
<div class="snippet-code">
<pre class="snippet-code-js lang-js prettyprint-override"><code>let finished = document.querySelectorAll( ".fin" );
let unfinished = document.querySelectorAll(".unfin");
let findiv = document.getElementById("fsqfeet");
let finTotal = 0;
let unfinTotal = 0;

for( let element of finished ) {
  element.addEventListener( "change", function() {
    // redundant
    // finished = document.querySelectorAll(".fin");
    for( let fin of finished ) {
    console.log( Number( fin.value ));
    finTotal += Number( fin.value );
    }
  });
}

asignListener( finished, 0 );
asignListener( unfinished, 1 );</code></pre>
<pre class="snippet-code-html lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;form action="/action_page.php" &gt;

&lt;fieldset&gt;
&lt;legend&gt;Square Footage Statistics:&lt;/legend&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Location&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Square Feet&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Previous Sq Feet&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Notes&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;div id="fsqfeet"&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;First Floor:&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;td&gt;&lt;input type="number" class="fin" id="ffsf" min="0" value="2000" autofocus&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Second Floor:&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;td&gt;&lt;input type="number" class="fin" id="sfsf" min="0" value="560"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Total Finished Sq Feet:&lt;/th&gt; 
    &lt;td&gt;&lt;output name="totalfinished"&gt;&lt;/output&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Garage:&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;td&gt;&lt;input type="number" class="unfin" id="gsf" min="0" value="200"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Covered Front Porch:&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;td&gt;&lt;input type="number" class="unfin" id="cfp" min="0" value="563"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Covered Back Porch:&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;td&gt;&lt;input type="number" class="unfin" id="cbp" min="0" value="80"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Covered Side Porch:&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;td&gt;&lt;input type="number" class="unfin" id="csp" min="0" value="90"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Total Unfinished Sq Feet:&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;td&gt;&lt;output name="totalunfinished"&gt;&lt;/output&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Grand Total Sq Feet:&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;td&gt;&lt;output name="gtsf" for="tusf thsf"&gt;&lt;/output&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/fieldset&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;</code></pre>
</div>
</div>
</p>
<p>Let's look at an improved version of the code (avoiding repetitions):</p>
<p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false" data-console="true" data-babel="false" data-babel-preset-react="false" data-babel-preset-ts="false">
<div class="snippet-code">
<pre class="snippet-code-js lang-js prettyprint-override"><code>let finished = document.querySelectorAll(".fin");
let unfinished = document.querySelectorAll(".unfin");
let finTotal = 0;
let outputs = document.querySelectorAll(".output");

function getPartial( element, index ) {
    finTotal = 0;
    for( let fin of element ) {
        finTotal += Number( fin.value );
    }
    outputs[ index ].innerText = finTotal;
    total();
}

function total() {
    outputs[ 2 ].innerText = Number( outputs[ 0 ].value ) + Number( outputs[ 1 ].value );
}

function asignListener( elements, index ) {   
    for( let element of elements ) { 
        element.addEventListener( "change", function() {
            getPartial( elements, index );
        });
    }
}

asignListener( finished, 0 );
asignListener( unfinished, 1 );</code></pre>
<pre class="snippet-code-html lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;!-- Here the changes are minimal, just add the --&gt;
&lt;!-- corresponding class to your “output.” --&gt;
&lt;form action="/action_page.php" &gt;

&lt;fieldset&gt;
&lt;legend&gt;Square Footage Statistics:&lt;/legend&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Location&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Square Feet&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Previous Sq Feet&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Notes&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;div id="fsqfeet"&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;First Floor:&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;td&gt;&lt;input type="number" class="fin" id="ffsf" min="0" value="2000" autofocus&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Second Floor:&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;td&gt;&lt;input type="number" class="fin" id="sfsf" min="0" value="560"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Total Finished Sq Feet:&lt;/th&gt; 
    &lt;td&gt;&lt;output class="output" name="totalfinished"&gt;&lt;/output&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Garage:&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;td&gt;&lt;input type="number" class="unfin" id="gsf" min="0" value="200"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Covered Front Porch:&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;td&gt;&lt;input type="number" class="unfin" id="cfp" min="0" value="563"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Covered Back Porch:&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;td&gt;&lt;input type="number" class="unfin" id="cbp" min="0" value="80"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Covered Side Porch:&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;td&gt;&lt;input type="number" class="unfin" id="csp" min="0" value="90"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Total Unfinished Sq Feet:&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;td&gt;&lt;output class="output" name="totalunfinished"&gt;&lt;/output&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;th&gt;Grand Total Sq Feet:&lt;/th&gt;
    &lt;td&gt;&lt;output class="output" name="gtsf" for="tusf thsf"&gt;&lt;/output&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/fieldset&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;</code></pre>
</div>
</div>

Brief explanation of the “JavaScript” code:</p>
<p>First, we obtain all elements of class “output”:</p>
<pre><code>let outputs = document.querySelectorAll(&quot;.output&quot;);
</code></pre>
<p>Then we create a function that receives an array of elements and assigns a listener to it.</p>
<p>As you can see, each element will call <strong>getPartial()</strong>, passing it the array of elements as arguments (since it will need to iterate over them to obtain the correct value), and the index that will help identify the corresponding output.</p>
<pre><code>function asignListener( elements, index ) {   
    for( let element of elements ) { 
        element.addEventListener( &quot;change&quot;, function() {
            getPartial( elements, index );
        });
    }
}
</code></pre>
<p>This function is really simple. It receives an array of elements that it will iterate over to obtain the value of <strong>finTotal</strong> (since it will receive multiple calls, we set <strong>finTotal</strong> to “0” before the <em>for</em> loop). Once the value is obtained, we assign it to the corresponding output with the <strong>innerText</strong> function. and then we call <strong>total</strong> to display the corresponding value.</p>
<pre><code>function getPartial( element, index ) {
    finTotal = 0;
    for( let fin of element ) {
        finTotal += Number( fin.value );
    }
    outputs[ index ].innerText = finTotal;
    total();
}
</code></pre>
<p>We assign the sum of the other outputs to the corresponding output.</p>
<pre><code>function total() {
    outputs[ 2 ].innerText = Number( outputs[ 0 ].value ) + Number( outputs[ 1 ].value );
}
</code></pre>
<p>Finally, we call <strong>asignListener</strong> with the corresponding <em>arrays</em> of elements.</p>
<pre><code>asignListener( finished, 0 );
asignListener( unfinished, 1 );
</code></pre>

Q: Android Studio - Failed to notify project evaluation listener error A: <p>For my particular case it was an issue with KSP when adding Room to my project:</p>
<p>In libs.versions.toml I had to align the kspPlugin version to the kotlinGradlePlugin version</p>
<pre><code>[versions]
kotlinGradlePlugin = &quot;2.2.20&quot;
# KSP Must be kept in sync with kotlinGradlePlugin
# active releases can be found here https://github.com/google/ksp/releases
kspPlugin = &quot;2.2.20-2.0.4&quot; 


[plugins]
kotlin-android = { id = &quot;org.jetbrains.kotlin.android&quot;, version.ref = &quot;kotlinGradlePlugin&quot; }
kotlinMultiplatform = { id = &quot;org.jetbrains.kotlin.multiplatform&quot;, version.ref = &quot;kotlinGradlePlugin&quot;
ksp = { id = &quot;com.google.devtools.ksp&quot;, version.ref = &quot;kspPlugin&quot; }
</code></pre>
